# LinkedIn provider

## Tool naming

All tools prefixed `linkedin_`. Register in `tools.go`, implement in `service.go` or dedicated `*_orchestrator.go` for composite reads.

## Gateway proxy

Use `proxy.go` / `linkedinGateway.requestJSON` — never call LinkedIn directly. Required headers: `Linkedin-Version`, `X-Restli-Protocol-Version`.

## Schemas and agent docs

- Input JSON schemas: functions in `tools.go` or `budget_pacer.go` (e.g. `getCampaignsSchema()`).
- Agent-facing metric/pivot catalog: `schema_docs.go`.
- Budget pacer playbook: [docs/linkedin-budget-pacer.md](../../docs/linkedin-budget-pacer.md).
- Keep schemas aligned with LinkedIn Ads Reporting API docs.

## Budget pacer (composite read)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `campaign_snapshot.go` | Parse campaign rows; shared with future writes |
| `budget_pacer_calc.go` | Pure pacing math (no HTTP) |
| `budget_pacer_orchestrator.go` | Fetch campaigns + analytics, join, rollups |
| `budget_pacer.go` | Types, input parser, tool schema/description |

## Pagination

Reuse patterns from `pagination.go` and `analytics_pagination.go`. Support `auto_paginate`, `page_size`, `page_token` where applicable. Cap auto-pagination pages (`maxAutoPaginatePages`).

## Tests

Add `*_test.go` for input parsing, pagination edge cases, pacing math, and schema helpers. Run: `go test ./internal/provider/linkedin/...`

## Analytics roadmap

See `docs/linkedin-analytics-roadmap.md` for planned and shipped analytics features.
